 motor=1 when vibrate_mode=1 and ring=1. So the correct behavior is to set motor=1 when vibrate_mode=1, which means I should remove the constraint that vibrate_mode=1 forces motor=0. Let\'s refactor to match the test expectation exactly. The solution is to ensure that when vibrate_mode=1, we set motor=1, and then the logic for the ring should be handled properly to not conflict with this. We can see the final test requires specific behavior where vibrate_mode=1 results in motor=1 and ringer=0 in most cases except the ones we\'re testing.",\n    "action_input": {\n        "command": "replace_content_by_matching",\n        "args": {\n            "old_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input logic ring,\\n    input logic vibrate_mode,\\n    output logic ringer,\\n    output logic motor\\n);\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        if (vibrate_mode) begin\\n            ringer = 0;\\n            motor = 0;\\n        end\\n        else if (ring) begin\\n            ringer = 1;\\n            motor = 0;\\n        end\\n        else begin\\n            ringer = 0;\\n            motor = 0;\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule",\n            "new_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input logic ring,\\n    input logic vibrate_mode,\\n    output logic ringer,\\n    output logic motor\\n);\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        if (vibrate_mode) begin\\n            ringer = 0;\\n            motor = 1;\\n        end\\n        else if (ring) begin\\n            ringer = 1;\\n            motor = 0;\\n        end\\n        else begin\\n            ringer = 0;\\n            motor = 0;\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule"\n        }\n    }\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nOutput after running given action:\n<action_output>\n{\n    "is_action_executed": true,\n    "is_syntax_pass": true,\n    "is_sim_pass": false,\n    "error_msg": "{\\n    \\"stdout\\": \\"VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for outpu